Class PacketDecoder

    • Constructor Detail

      • PacketDecoder

        public PacketDecoder()
              throws java.net.UnknownHostException
        Creates a PacketDecoder listening for packets on the default address and port.

        The default address and port is the HEARTBEAT address and port from spx.sc.net.DefaultAddresses and spx.sc.net.DefaultPorts.

        The address and port to listen on may be changed using the setAddress method.

        To receive packets from the network the class may be run using the Runnable interface, or the pollSocket method may be called at frequent intervals.

        If the pollSocket method is being used, then the interval between calls must be short (~10ms), otherwise packets are likely to be missed.

        If this PacketDecoder is no longer required, the close function must be called to close the network socket.

        Throws:
        java.net.UnknownHostException - If hostname cannot be found.
        See Also:
        setAddress(java.lang.String, int), setAddress(java.net.InetAddress, int), pollSocket(), DefaultAddresses

      • installHandler

        public void installHandler(PacketDecoder.DecodeFn fn,
                           int packetType)
        Installs a packet decoder handler for a specific type of packet.

        The handler will be called for each packet received that is of the specified type.

        If a packetType of 0 is specified the handler is installed as a default that will be used whenever a packet is received that does not have a specific handler installed.

        Parameters:
        fn - The interface object containing the callback method to call when a packet of the specified type is received.
        packetType - Type of packet.
        See Also:
        Type

      • pollSocket

        public void pollSocket()
                throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Polls the network socket for new data.

        Any received packets are added to queue to be decoded in another thread.

        This method may be invoked by installing the PacketDecoder in a thread: 

         PacketDecoder packetDecoder = new PacketDecoder();
 Thread thread = new Thread(packetDecoder);
 packetDecoderThread.start();

        Alternatively, the pollSocket method may be manually called at regular intervals. The intervals should be kept small (~10ms) to prevent the loss of packets.

        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - If the packet list was in use while adding packets.

      • decodePacket

        public void decodePacket(java.net.DatagramPacket packet)
                  throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Decodes a specified packet.

        This method is used internally by the PacketDecoder class to decode packets received on the network.

        It may also be used to decode packets received from a source other than the address and port on which the PacketDecoder is listening.

        Parameters:
        packet - The packet to decode.
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - If the packet list is in use.
